Networking tools commands

01.) ping - to check reachability of a host on an internet protocol
example :- ping www.google.com

02.) traceroute or traceroute6 - to display route and measure transit delays of packets across an internet protocol network
example :- traceroute www.google.com

03.) Netstat - to display active network connections, route tables, interface statistics, masquerade connections multicast memberships
example :- netstat -a

04.) Nmap - To discover hosts and services on a computer network, creating a map of the network
example :- nmap -p 1-1000 target

05.) tcpdump - to capture and analyze network traffic
example :- tcpdump -i eth0

06.) ipconfig (windows) or ifconfig(linux) - to display configuration of network interfaces
example :- ifconfig

07.) dig (domain information groper) - to query dns name servers for information about host addresses, mail exchanges, name servers and related information
example :- dig www.google.com

08.) nslookup (windows) or host (linux) - to query dns servers for domain information
 


